-- Peru to Call Bids for Jungle Power Plants on May 10
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-02T14:16:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/peru-to-call-bids-for-jungle-power-plants-on-may-10.html
Peru  will call bids to build and
operate two gas-fired power plants in the Amazon jungle on May
10, state news agency  Andina  reported.  A unit of  Actividades de Construccion y Servicios SA  and
the groups Energias del Peru and Servicios Integrales de Energia
have qualified to bid for the 20-year power plant concessions,
which will generate a combined 68 megawatts in the cities of
Pucallpa and Puerto Maldonado, the agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
